Author: Emanuil Rusev <hello@erusev.com>
Date:   Fri Jun 5 14:49:26 2026 +0300

    Nudge to brew upgrade when the external CLI is too old

    When the resolved binary is a too-old external install (e.g. Homebrew), the
    app can't update it, so it surfaces a non-blocking nudge in the menu --
    "Update llama.cpp … brew upgrade llama.cpp" with a Re-check action -- while
    still starting the server, since an older build usually works (warn, don't
    block).

    To support this, status()'s .ready now carries the version (feeding the
    footer without a second read), and the readiness check became a full matrix:
    install when missing, reinstall an outdated app-owned binary, nudge an
    outdated external one. The menu's retry/re-check share one path
    (LBRecheckCLI), so re-checking after a brew upgrade clears the nudge and
    restarts the server on the new binary.
