Author: Emanuil Rusev <hello@erusev.com>
Date:   Fri Jun 5 11:58:58 2026 +0300

    Resolve the llama binary and classify who owns it

    Replace the hardcoded /opt/homebrew/bin assumption with a resolver that
    classifies the install: app-owned (the ~/.installama curl-install path the
    app may update), external (e.g. Homebrew -- use but never modify), or
    missing (install flow needed). This is the foundation for the app
    installing and updating its own CLI.

    Also collapse the stale separate-binary assumption: the install ships one
    unified `llama` executable, so `serve` and `fit-params` are subcommands of
    it rather than standalone `llama-server` / `llama-fit-params` binaries.
    LlamaServer and MemProfile now drive the resolved `llama` path.
