commit 623b6a94bca2ed2c6a300768a637ef065d89e106
Author: Emanuil Rusev <hello@erusev.com>
Date:   Tue Jun 2 15:20:36 2026 +0300

    Make download delegate self-contained; drop main-actor sync hops

    The URLSession delegate callbacks ran on a background queue but reached
    back into the main actor synchronously (DispatchQueue.main.sync) to read
    the model, HF cache dir, and download plan. Those blocking hops were a
    standing deadlock hazard and made the delegate's concurrency hard to
    reason about.

    Each of those values is fixed once a download starts, so snapshot them
    into PartialWriter at creation time. The delegate now sources everything
    from the writer and never blocks on the main actor -- it only fires
    DispatchQueue.main.async for UI/state updates, giving a clean
    one-directional boundary. findManagedModel is no longer needed and is
    removed.

    The writers dictionary and its serial queue move into a dedicated
    WriterTable type, so the shared mutable state has a single owner instead
    of a raw nonisolated(unsafe) field on the otherwise main-actor
    ModelManager. The serial queue is kept deliberately: streaming writes
    must stay ordered, which an actor's unordered task scheduling would not
    guarantee.

    Verified by live download against the dev build: a resume-from-partial
    run completed with correct blob promotion, snapshot symlink, and
    models.ini regeneration.
