Date:   Fri Apr 17 16:33:01 2026 +0300

    Fix sideloaded MoE compatibility using measured resident memory

    Compatibility math used file size × overheadMultiplier as the weight-memory
    estimate. For MoE models the GGUF file size overestimates runtime memory,
    leaving no budget headroom for KV cache and capping context tiers well
    below what the hardware supports.

    llama-fit-params already measures actual resident memory. The parser was
    extracting only the KV component and discarding the model + compute
    numbers. It also only read MTL0 and Host devices, ignoring CPU_REPACK
    where MoE expert weights spill on Apple Silicon.

    Parser now takes the final breakdown iteration and sums model + compute
    across every device row. CatalogEntry gets a new fitResidentBytes field
    populated from fit-params for sideloaded models; compatibility uses it
    when available, falling back to file size for catalog entries (which are
    evaluated pre-download and have no fit-params data).
