    Implement 'Sleep when idle' workaround and fix menu-open unloads

    - The --sleep-idle-seconds option in llama-server unloads models from memory but doesn't update the /models endpoint, leaving the UI out of sync.
    - Added polling of /props endpoint in LlamaServer.swift to detect sleeping models and explicitly trigger an unload to synchronize state.
    - Optimized ModelManager.updatePresetsFile() to skip redundant writes/reloads if the content hasn't changed. This prevents models from unloading every time the menu is opened.
    - Added a settings observer to LlamaServer so that changes to the idle timeout are applied immediately via a server reload.
