Author: Emanuil Rusev <hello@erusev.com>
Date:   Thu Dec 18 21:11:56 2025 +0200

    Remove memory limit option

    Removed the memory limit option because it confused users. People asked why specific values like 2, 3, and 4 GB were chosen, whether these were device-specific, why they couldn't set it to 5 GB, and what would happen to models they already installed if they lowered the limit.

    The option also added a lot of complexity to the code, especially around handling installed models that might exceed a new lower limit. By using a fixed safety budget instead (50% of system memory, or 75% for 128GB+ devices), get a simpler, more predictable app.
