    Add user-configurable memory usage cap setting

    Added a new "Memory cap" setting to the menu, allowing users to control the maximum RAM allocation for models. This replaces the previous hard-coded logic that allocated 50% of RAM for systems <128GB and 75% for ≥128GB.

    The setting uses a segmented control with options based on eighths of system RAM:
    - Low memory (<128GB): 2/8 (25%), 3/8 (37.5%), 4/8 (50%)
    - High memory (≥128GB): 2/8 (25%), 4/8 (50%), 6/8 (75%)

    Displays actual GB values (e.g., "4 GB") sorted from smallest to largest. Defaults to the highest available option (4/8 for <128GB, 6/8 for ≥128GB).

